properties.headline: Hydrologic Outlook issued January 9 at 9:43AM CST by NWS Chicago IL
properties.description:
Rainfall is expected over portions of the Mississippi
Valley, Midwest, and Great Lakes Regions beginning today and
continuing into the weekend. A Flood Watch is effect for areas
expected to receive the heaviest rainfall, generally along and
southeast of I-55. Although the Rock and Fox River Basins are not
expected to receive heavy liquid precipitation at this time, very
wet antecedent conditions mean that the area remains vulnerable to
rainfall. A relatively small change to the track of the upcoming
weather system could change the amount of precipitation that falls
as rain rather than snow or ice. If more rainfall occurs than
currently forecasted, large rises on waterways in the Rock and Fox
Basins could occur.

This outlook means that elevated water levels and potential
impacts are possible. Persons should closely monitor the latest
forecasts.

NWSheadline: Heavy rainfall late this week may lead to flooding
